This bill would allow college graduates to roll federal student loan debt into a home mortgage through the purchase of a federally-owned vacant property. This lowers interest rates for borrowers, supports local economies & strengthens the housing market. https://axne.house.gov/media/press-releases/axne-colleagues-introduce-bill-help-college-graduates-purchase-homes …

Owning a home is part of the American dream, but this can be near impossible for Iowans crushed by student loans. Today, I introduced legislation that creates a pathway to home-ownership for college graduates strapped with debt.

I’ve heard from rural health care providers across #IA03 who consistently tell me that staffing shortages remain a top issue. If a rural hospital doesn’t have the available staff for direct supervision, it can limit the type of care Iowans can receive in our rural communities.

Our bill postpones implementation of “direct supervision” – or the requirement that a physician or nonphysician practitioner be physically present – for outpatient therapeutic services at rural hospitals until 2021.

I'm proud to have joined @RepAdrianSmith to introduce bipartisan legislation to provide relief to our rural hospitals by delaying enforcement of burdensome regulations.  https://axne.house.gov/media/press-releases/reps-axne-smith-introduce-bipartisan-rural-hospital-relief-bill … pic.twitter.com/Oylltk1w0D

Members of Congress should be working for their constituents, not for themselves or for special interests. We should be focused on cracking down on political corruption that is hurting Iowa families and holding Washington accountable, not on giving ourselves a pay raise.

Last week, I introduced an ethics package to end corruption in Washington and hold politicians accountable. Democrats have proposed a pay raise as part of a larger spending bill. I stood up to my own party and signed onto an amendment to stop this increase from going into effect. pic.twitter.com/EztwHRY3rP

I'm fighting for access to affordable housing and I plan to hold bad housing actors accountable. Today, I sent a letter to a Utah investment firm which purchased 5 mobile home communities in Iowa and is now dramatically raising rents on Iowans. @KCCINews https://www.kcci.com/article/residents-facing-massive-rent-hike-hope-for-help-from-washington/27890276 …

Today, I sent a letter to the investment group, Havenpark Capital, which has received an "F" grade from the Better Business Bureau, demanding answers regarding the justification for these massive and unrealistic spikes in rent. https://axne.house.gov/media/press-releases/rep-axne-seeks-answers-regarding-rent-spikes-iowa-mobile-home-communities …

In addition to massive rent spikes, residents are dealing with an 11 page list of outrageous rules like limiting swing sets & play areas in yards, prohibiting toys from being left in yards, and placing a 35lb weight limit on pets. Some residents might have to give up their dogs.

After an out-of-state investment firm purchased manufactured housing communities (MHCs) in Iowa, residents are facing massive rent increases. Today, I invited @SenSherrodBrown to join me in visiting residents at an MHC in Waukee to talk abt the financial hardship this will cause. pic.twitter.com/vViGArtDIL

Thank you Chris for speaking with us. As I mentioned today, I'm going to look into this and plan to hold any bad housing actors accountable. https://twitter.com/chris50263/status/1138072401454014465 …

Together, we're fighting to make Washington work for Iowans, not special interests. https://www.radioiowa.com/2019/06/06/axne-says-clean-up-congress-act-includes-lifetime-lobbying-ban-for-lawmakers/ …

My Clean Up Congress Act would 1) prevent member pay raises until Congress reduces the deficit to zero; 2) prohibit members from using taxpayer dollars on first class flights; and 3) institute a lifetime ban on members becoming lobbyists. #CleanUpCongressAct #IA03
Today, I introduced an ethics reform package to restore public trust in Congress and ensure that elected officials in Washington are working for their constituents, not for special interests.
